IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDescription: TO PROTECT THE PUBLIC BY ASSESSING COMPETENCIES FOR OSTEOPATHIC MEDICINE.
IRS990.MissionDescription: TO PROTECT THE PUBLIC BY PROVIDING THE MEANS TO ASSESS COMPETENCIES FOR OSTEOPATHIC MEDICINE AND RELATED HEALTH CARE PROFESSIONS.
IRS990.Description: TESTING OF OSTEOPATHIC MEDICAL STUDENTS - PREPARATION AND ADMINISTRATION OF EXAMS TESTING THE COMPETENCY OF INDIVIDUALS SEEKING LICENSES AS OSTEOPATHIC PHYSICIANS. APPROXIMATELY 22,000 STUDENTS WERE TESTED IN 2012.

Activity2.Description: SPECIALTY BOARD TESTING - PREPARATION OF MEDICAL SPECIALTY COLLEGE EXAMS. APPROXIMATELY 23,000 STUDENTS WERE TESTED IN 2012.

Activity3.Description: TRANSCRIPT SERVICES - ISSUING CERTIFICATION OF PRIOR EXAM RESULTS. APPROXIMATELY 9,700 TRANSCRIPTS WERE REQUESTED IN 2012.

Form990ScheduleDPartXIII.Identifier: DESCRIPTION OF UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS UNDER FIN 48:
Form990ScheduleDPartXIII.Explanation: THE ORGANIZATION IS A NOT-FOR-PROFIT ORGANIZATION EXEMPT FROM PAYING CORPORATE FEDERAL INCOME TAX UNDER SECTION 501(C)(3) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE. IT HAS BEEN CLASSIFIED AS AN ORGANIZATION THAT IS NOT A PRIVATE FOUNDATION UNDER THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE AND CHARITABLE CONTRIBUTIONS BY DONORS ARE TAX DEDUCTIBLE. THE ORGANIZATION HAS EVALUATED ITS TAX POSITIONS AND DETERMINED IT HAS NO UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS AT DECEMBER 31, 2012 AND 2011. THE ORGANIZATION'S 2009, 2010 AND 2011 TAX YEARS ARE OPEN FOR EXAMINATION BY THE IRS. SHOULD THE ORGANIZATION'S TAX EXEMPT STATUS BE CHALLENGED IN THE FUTURE, ALL YEARS SINCE INCEPTION COULD BE SUBJECT TO REVIEW BY THE IRS. IT IS THE ORGANIZATION'S POLICY TO INCLUDE ANY PENALTIES AND INTEREST RELATED TO INCOME TAXES IN MANAGEMENT AND GENERAL EXPENSES, HOWEVER, THE ORGANIZATION HAS NO PENALTIES OR INTEREST RELATED TO INCOME TAXES.

GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 2
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THREE EMPLOYEES OF THE ORGANIZATION ARE FAMILY MEMBERS OF AN OFFICER(S). SEE DISCLOSURE INCLUDED IN SCHEDULE L.

GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: ORGANIZATION'S PROCESS TO REVIEW: FORM 990 THE FORM 990 IS POSTED TO THE NBOME SHAREPOINT AND AN EMAIL IS SENT TO EACH BOARD MEMBER INFORMING THEM THAT IT IS AVAILABLE FOR THEIR REVIEW. QUESTIONS OR CONCERNS THAT ANY BOARD MEMBERS HAVE ARE DIRECTED TO THE CFO AND ARE ADDRESSED BEFORE THE FORM 990 IS FILED.

GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: COMMITTEE AND BOARD MEMBERS ARE REQUIRED TO SIGN DISCLOSURE AND CONFIDENTIALITY STATEMENTS AT EACH MEETING. IF A POTENTIAL CONFLICT OF INTEREST ARISES, IT IS DISCUSSED WITH THE CHAIR OF THE BOARD. IF IT IS DEEMED TO BE A CONFLICT, THE INDIVIDUAL IS ASKED TO LEAVE DURING ANY RELATED DISCUSSIONS.

GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15A
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE FINANCE COMMITTEE, EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE, AND BOARD OF DIRECTORS APPROVE THE COMPENSATION PACKAGE UPON HIRE AFTER COMPARING THE COMPENSATION TO DATA FROM LOCAL AND NATIONAL COMPENSATION STUDIES AS WELL AS COMPARING TO SIMILAR ORGANIZATIONS COMPENSATION DATA.

GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE ORGANIZATION DOES NOT MAKE ITS BYLAWS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY OR FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC.
THERE HAS BEEN NO CHANGES TO THE OVERSIGHT OR SELECTION PROCESSES FOR THE INDEPENDENT ACCOUNTANT FROM PRIOR YEAR PRACTICES.
